direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: the substances that you take into your body as food and the way that they influence your health

examination_example.sentence: I use my bimonthly weigh-in results to get information about my <highlight>nutrition</highlight> as well.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我也用我两月一次的称重结果来获得我的营养信息。

examination_example.sentence: The immune system of the body under stress or through lack of <highlight>nutrition</highlight> or exercise can be weakened.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 处于压力下、缺乏营养或锻炼，身体的免疫系统会被削弱。

examination_example.sentence: Alexandra Johnstone, professor of appetite research at the University of Aberdeen, argues that it may simply be because breakfast-skippers have been found to be less knowledgeable about <highlight>nutrition</highlight> and health.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 阿伯丁大学食欲研究教授 Alexandra Johnstone 认为，这可能只是因为不吃早餐的人，对营养和健康的知识了解比较少。

examination_example.sentence: They allow the animal to rely on sunshine for its <highlight>nutrition</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们让动物可以依靠阳光获取营养。

examination_example.sentence: James Bentham, a co-author of the research from Imperial College, London, says the global trend is likely to be due primarily to improvements in <highlight>nutrition</highlight> and healthcare.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 来自伦敦帝国理工学院的研究报告合著者 James Bentham 表示，这一全球趋势可能主要是由于营养和医疗保健的改善。

examination_example.sentence: As a physician, <highlight>nutrition</highlight> is one of the most powerful things you can change to reverse the effects of long-term disease.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作为一名医生，营养是你可以改变长期疾病的影响的最强有力的事情之一。
